{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## Plan-review triage (PASS, 20 advisories) — 2026-07-01\n\nOAuth App created by operator; Client ID + Client Secret are in SSM at\n/rebar/prod/github-oauth-client-{id,secret} (verified readable, non-CHANGEME).\nAWS access restored this session; GitHub still lacks admin:org (org OAuth App was\nthe operator's manual step — done).\n\nDecision: the advisories converge on one truth — the runbook over-promised SSM→config\nautomation the scripts don't yet do. Remediating by IMPLEMENTING that automation (not\ndowngrading the runbook to manual), which is the point of this ticket.\n\nValid → fixing in the code half of WS8:\n- adv 1,2,4,6,8,10,11,12 (dup cluster): fetch-secrets.sh + compose-up.sh don't materialize\n  the OAuth params. FIX: fetch both into .env; substitute client-id into gerrit.config;\n  write client-secret into secure.config (0600); fail-loud if absent under auth.type=OAUTH.\n- adv 3,5,9,14,17,18: install-plugins.sh only handles events-log; no pinned oauth.jar +\n  sha256. FIX: add an oauth.jar install block (pinned URL + sha256, events-log discipline);\n  record real artifact + sha256 in plugins/README.md (research agent resolving the 3.14\n  artifact now).\n- adv 15: user_data.sh PARAMS array is a second unenumerated consumer. FIX: add both params.\n- adv 7: bootstrap-gerrit-admin.sh uses the dev-login endpoint that dies under OAUTH.\n  FIX: document post-OAUTH bootstrap (bot HTTP password) in the runbook.\n- adv 16: GitHub-outage blast radius. FIX: add a break-glass section to the runbook.\n- adv 19: account-migration idempotency. FIX: state the migration is idempotent (skip\n  already-migrated external-ids) in the runbook.\n- adv 20: no file_impact. FIX: set_file_impact recorded (8 paths).\n\nJudged lower-priority / deferred with justification:\n- adv 13 (stand up a local Docker Gerrit 3.14 spike before cutover): heavyweight. Mitigated\n  by (a) compose-up.sh failing loud if oauth.jar is absent under OAUTH, and (b) the runbook\n  Step-6 clean-boot + login verification BEFORE proceeding to WS7. The live install-then-verify\n  IS the compatibility check; a rollback path is documented. Noted as residual risk."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782930623699737001,"uuid":"a7424522-555b-4b78-9294-dfbeb06efef6"}